==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forethought
<hw>Fore"thought`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Thought of, or
planned, beforehand; aforethought; prepense; hence, deliberate.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Forethought</xex> malice.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forethought</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forethought
<hw>Fore"thought`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A thinking or planning
beforehand; prescience; premeditation; forecast; provident
care.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A sphere that will demand from him <qex>forethought</qex>,
courage, and wisdom.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forethoughtful</ent>⟦br⟧
